doc.after: Boeing and Lockheed Martin announced their intent to form the United Launch Alliance joint venture on May 2 2005 3 ULA merges the production of the government space launch services of the two companies into one central plant in Decatur Alabama and merged all engineering into another central plant in Littleton Colorado Boeing Integrated Defense Systems Delta IV and Lockheed Martin Space Systems Atlas V are both launchers developed for the Evolved Expendable Launch Vehicle program intended to provide the United States government with competitively priced assured access to space
